# Gather Architecture

## Monorepo Structure

```
gather/
├── apps/api/      # Express backend (Node.js + TypeScript)
├── apps/web/      # Vite + React frontend
├── packages/shared/  # Shared types (User, AuthResponse, etc.)
└── prisma/        # Schema + migrations
```

## Tech Stack

- **Backend:** Express, TypeScript, Prisma, PostgreSQL (Supabase)
- **Frontend:** React 18, Vite, Tailwind CSS, react-router-dom
- **Auth:** JWT (access 15min, refresh 7 days) + httpOnly cookie
- **Database:** Prisma ORM, Supabase Postgres (transaction + direct pooler URLs)

## Key Conventions

- **API routes:** `/api/auth/*`, `/api/users/*` — Express router modules in `apps/api/src/routes/`
- **Auth middleware:** `authenticateToken` in `apps/api/src/middleware/auth.ts`
- **Shared types:** Import from `@gather/shared` (User, AuthResponse)
- **Env vars:** Root `.env` — `DATABASE_URL`, `DIRECT_URL`, `ACCESS_TOKEN_SECRET`, `OAUTH_ENCRYPTION_KEY`, `PORT`, `CORS_ORIGIN`
- **Naming:** Descriptive files (e.g. `availabilityMatchingEngine.ts` not `utils.ts`)

## Data Flow

- Web proxies `/api` to API (port 3001) in dev
- Auth: register/login return `accessToken` + set refresh cookie; protected routes use `Authorization: Bearer <token>`
- Prisma client: `apps/api/src/lib/prisma.ts` — use `prisma` singleton
